posts.title: If you ever wonder how bad Communism is - government here is trying to take 68% of my paycheck! (Quebec)
posts.content:
I live in Quebec. Quebec is a communist province. Around half of quebecers are communist and either don't work, study for some useless degree or work for the government. The other half has to carry all the weight, and this include insane taxes.

I am a high school teacher. In 2024, I will net $100,000, but only because I worked a shitton of overtime. Already this year, I will be paying 44% in taxes + deductions. That's right: 44% of my pay stolen at source, and probably another 1-2% when it's time to file because of "taxable benefits."

Anyway, the issue begins in 2025. In 2025, I will have to redeem a $200,000 capital gain. I literally have no way to avoid it. Already, I will have to pay $30,000 in taxes (including around 5k in added "deductions") for the privilege of getting back my own money.

The real problem (or at least, the second real problem) comes when it comes to tax brackets. $200,000 is enough to push me into a super-high tax bracket. Not the highest, mind you, because the highest is 53.31%. Yes, you read that right.

This means that out of the 100,000 I would earn as a teacher:

  1. 45% goes directly into taxes
  2. 6% goes into provincial retirement plan (a huge scam)
  3. Another 8% goes into another retirement plan (another huge scam)
  4. 2% goes to the union
  5. 1.5% employment insurance (paying so other people don't work)
  6. 0.5% goes into parental insurance (paying so other people can have kids and be paid for it)
  7. 3% goes into medical/other BS insurance I never use

And I have to pay another 2% taxes for "tax benefits". In total, because I have a huge capital gain, 68% of my pay is taken from me. Deducted at source.

Of course, I still need to pay gas, parking, car maintenance, winter tires, et cetera. I pay around $1,000 a year for classroom material as well (supplies, prizes to win like cinema ticket, christmas cookies, etc).

Even not counting that, I am left with... 32% of my pay. This means waking up, going to work, slaving away with kids (some with huge problems), being bossed by feminists (muh pronouns), doing overtime sometimes until 10 PM (my base salary is 70k a year), working on week-ends, planning classes, etc etc, for...

... 32k net a year. 2600$ net per month. That's in canadian dollar, so in US dollar, thats 22,000$ net per year.

Do you really think I want to do that? Freeze my hands removing the snow from my car? Be stuck in useless meeting discussing DEI propaganda? Grading 150+ copies of the same thing? Managing 38 kids in a classroom, half with behavorial problems? Dealing with school BS, having to work for activities, etc etc.?

"But but but you are getting a huge capital gain!" This is a once-in-a-lifetime event. It won't happen again, probably ever. God forbid I get 170k once in my life.

Given all that, I have chosen not to work in 2025. I will be either taking a sabbatical, or resigning.

What's the point of even working at this point?? I don't fucking get it.

/endrant.
